Ex- freedom fighters met in Nyeri town on Tuesday when they prayed for peace in the country as the General Election nears.More than 300 Mau Mau freedom fighters met at Kabiruini grounds in Nyeri county. They said the country must remain peaceful before, during and after the August 8 election for a stable economy.The former freedom fighters were led by General Duncan Kariuki. They also urged politicians to stop insulting President Uhuru Kenyatta, saying there is need to respect the Office of The President. They also promised to support the government of the day.The prayer meeting was attended by elders from Nyeri, Nakuru and Kiambu counties, among others.Among those who attended the prayer meeting were 12 elderly men who have been fasting and praying for the country in Aberdare Forest.